library(ggpmisc)

tb_dat_1 <- analysis_dat %>% 
  group_by(advertiser_binary) %>% 
  summarize(`Avg. Incivility` = round(mean(TOXICITY), 2),
            `Total Ads` = n()) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  rename(`Advertiser Type` = advertiser_binary)

tb_dat_2 <- analysis_dat %>% 
  count(toxic, advertiser_binary) %>%
  group_by(advertiser_binary) %>%
  mutate(total = sum(n)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(perc = round(n/total*100, 2)) %>%
  filter(toxic == 1) %>% 
  rename(`Advertiser Type` = advertiser_binary) %>% 
  mutate(`% Incivil` = perc) %>% 
  select(`Advertiser Type`, `% Incivil`)

tb_dat <- tb_dat_1 %>% 
  left_join(tb_dat_2) %>% 
  # arrange(`Advertiser Type`) %>% 
  mutate(`Advertiser Type` = ifelse(`Advertiser Type` != "Outside Groups", "Official Campaigns", `Advertiser Type`)) %>% 
  select(`Advertiser Type`, `Total Ads`, everything())

ggtable <- tibble(x = 0.98, y = 150000, tb = list(tb_dat))


analysis_dat %>%  
  # mutate(type = fct_relevel(type, ad_subtypes)) %>% 
  arrange(type) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(TOXICITY, fill = advertiser_binary)) +
  geom_histogram(alpha = 0.95) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(x = "\nAd Incivility (Probability)", y = "Count\n") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0.5, linetype = "dashed") +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::label_number()) +
  scale_fill_grey(name = "Advertiser Type", start = 0.8, end = 0.2) +
  geom_table(data = ggtable, aes(x, y, label = tb))

Targeting

targeting_count_1 <- analysis_dat %>% 
  count(targetedness_hl_1m, advertiser_binary) %>% 
  group_by(advertiser_binary) %>% 
  mutate(total = sum(n)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  filter(targetedness_hl_1m == 1) %>% 
  mutate(perc = round(n/total*100, 2)) %>% 
  select(`Advertiser Type` = advertiser_binary, `Total Ads` = total, `% Targeted below 1m` = perc)

targeting_count_2 <- analysis_dat %>% 
  count(targetedness_hl_50k, advertiser_binary) %>% 
  group_by(advertiser_binary) %>% 
  mutate(total = sum(n)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  filter(targetedness_hl_50k == 1) %>% 
  mutate(perc = round(n/total*100, 2)) %>% 
  select(`Advertiser Type` = advertiser_binary, `% Targeted below 50k` = perc)

targeting_count_3 <- analysis_dat %>% 
  count(targetedness_hl_1k, advertiser_binary) %>% 
  group_by(advertiser_binary) %>% 
  mutate(total = sum(n)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  filter(targetedness_hl_1k == 1) %>% 
  mutate(perc = round(n/total*100, 2)) %>% 
  select(`Advertiser Type` = advertiser_binary, `% Targeted below 1k` = perc)


targeting_count <- targeting_count_1 %>% 
  left_join(targeting_count_2) %>% 
  left_join(targeting_count_3)
  
ggtable_t <- tibble(x = 1, y = 300000, tb = list(targeting_count))

analysis_dat %>% 
  count(targetedness_hl_1m, toxic) %>% 
  group_by(targetedness_hl_1m) %>% 
  mutate(total = sum(n)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(perc = n/total) %>% 
  filter(toxic == 1) %>% 
  mutate(toxic = ifelse(toxic == 1, "Incivil", "Civil")) %>% 
  mutate(targetedness_hl_1m =  ifelse(targetedness_hl_1m == 1, "Below 1 million", "Above 1 million")) %>% 
  mutate(targetedness_hl_1m = fct_relevel(targetedness_hl_1m, "Below 1 million")) %>% 
  mutate(n_lab = scales::label_comma(big.mark = " ")(n)) %>% 
  mutate(perc_label = paste0(round(perc*100, 2), "%", " (", n_lab,")")) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(targetedness_hl_1m, perc)) +
  geom_col(fill = "lightgrey", width = 0.5) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)) +
  geom_text(aes(label = perc_label), nudge_y = 0.001) +
  labs(x = "\nTargeting", y = "Percent Incivil\n") +
  theme_minimal()

mod1_glm <- glm(targetedness_hl_1m ~ toxic, data = analysis_dat, family = binomial())

mod2_glm <- glm(targetedness_hl_1m ~ toxic + affil  + advertiser_binary + age + gender + max_reached_log + 
                  add_runs_log + num_days_log + closeness_to_election_log + spd_lower_bound_log
                  , data = analysis_dat, family = binomial())

mod3_glm <- glm(targetedness_hl_1m ~ advertiser_binary*toxic  + affil +  
                  max_reached_log + age +
                  gender + add_runs_log  + closeness_to_election_log +
                  num_days_log + spd_lower_bound_log, data = analysis_dat, family = binomial())

interaction_data <- readRDS("out/interaction_data_1m.rds")

gg_1m <- interaction_data %>% 
  as_tibble() %>% 
  mutate(x = ifelse(x == 1, "Political Campaigns", "Outside Groups")) %>%
  mutate(x = fct_relevel(x, "Political Campaigns")) %>% 
  mutate(Incivil = ifelse(group == 1, "Yes", "No"))

gg_1m %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x, predicted, color = Incivil)) +
  geom_point(position = position_dodge(width = 0.25)) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = conf.low, ymax = conf.high), position = position_dodge(width = 0.25), width = 0.1) +
  coord_flip() +
  scale_x_discrete(expand=c(0.8, 0)) +
  geom_text(aes(label = round(predicted, 3)), show.legend = F, size = 3.2) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(x = "Advertiser Type\n", y = "\nPredicted probabilities of Targeting below 1m") +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("darkgrey", "black")) +
  theme(legend.position = "top")

Comp

# define a helper function to extract SE from glm output
se.coef <- function(glm.output){sqrt(diag(vcov(glm.output)))}


#Get the odds ratio
OR_1 <- exp(coef(mod1_glm3)) #%>% .[-1]

# Then, we can get the `StdErr.OR` by multiplying the two:
Std.Error.OR_1 <-  OR_1 * se.coef(mod1_glm3)# %>% .[-1]

#Get the odds ratio
OR_2 <- exp(coef(mod2_glm3)) #%>% .[-1]

# Then, we can get the `StdErr.OR` by multiplying the two:
Std.Error.OR_2 <-  OR_2 * se.coef(mod2_glm3) #%>% .[-1]
